haikus.content:
Last haiku of March 
This one will stay on the page 
Better make it count...

Afternoon weight-lift 
Tearing muscles to repair 
The body is weird

Start of the quarter 
Husted from the bike ride in 
Time for some coffee

I worked out for once 
Not much to look at just yet 
My taxes are done

Sleep in, chores, leave late 
Slaying monsters in dungeons 
Will never get old

Watching viking dudes  
Laundry, cut grass, other chores 
Saturday goes by

Don't move. Please, don't move 
Giving scritches while watching... 
Injured kitty sleeps

Writing poetry 
Someone behind me, quiet 
Sharing an office

Riding in the car 
Got a hole in his back leg 
Charlie, hurt again

More and more and more 
He is always wanting more 
This cat always screm

Battery is low 
Plugged it in expectantly... 
Great, its not charging

D&D with friends 
This party can't fight giants 
They run every time

Eggs bacon and toast 
Clean wheels, movie after lunch 
Saturday is nice

Splitting my notebooks 
More complex than I first thought 
All this for figures

Moving furniture 
More room for activities 
Great, now there's a glare

Halfway through the week 
Running errands fucking blows 
Now go make dinner

Got my new ID 
I hope it works for the bus  
It probably won't

Back to modeling 
No, not that kind of model 
Glacier prethicktor

Coding on the couch 
Concatenating tables 
This time with money

Sleepy cuddle day 
Lasagna and games with friends 
After cleaning up

Morning sun, blinding 
At home all alone, waiting 
Kitty's wine must flow

All alone today 
Not even home with Bubby 
Traffic was a bitch

Lost motivation 
Hunger claws at my stomach 
I should eat some lunch

Legs feel like jelly 
Riding all the way to work 
Was a bad idea

Low clouds on my walk 
Jeans and pajamas are warm 
I'll work out later

Another long drive 
This time I'm going back home 
Then, more vidya

Woken by the sun 
Frost covers the ground outside 
Vidya, inside

Missing my Kitty 
Long drive to see family 
Worthwhile in the end

Riding in the rain 
My bike is brand spanking new 
I hope I don't die

Fancy suit and tie 
Not as pretty as the wife 
Time to give money

Grandmas are coming 
Time to put down the baby 
Let them deal with her

Native words are tough 
I wish the past was not so 
We could be much more

Hiding from the sun 
Unintentionally, though 
Lots of trips outside

An extra hour 
Can make all the difference 
From dawn until dusk

In and out all day 
No time to do anything... 
It's not about me

An exciting drive 
Loud yelps, sweet breath, and kisses 
Her name is Desna

Clouds give way to sun 
Four legs, two legs, all walking 
Our animal bonds

Last school day until 
we bring home a new puppy 
New dog for our dog

Writing is not hard 
Just stare at a page until 
You bleed from your eyes

Meeting, teach, study 
Wednesday is my day to do 
No more, with puppy

Muscles burn this morn 
Resting on my feet all day 
Hungry, so hungry

Teaching takes up time 
I want to code all day long 
Balance, harmony

Mowed the lawn again 
Here we go around the sun 
Different each time

Practical magic 
Chicken wings and mimosas 
I love Saturdays

Office hours missed 
Why do I even bother 
Now there's a cat door

Haikus can be hard 
Sometimes they do not make sense 
Refrigerator

Bike to a meeting 
Run all the way home again 
Always modify

More roughage for lunch 
In a dark classroom all day 
What is for dinner?

Soft spots all up top 
I wanted solar panels 
Now we need a roof

Old games and new chores 
Hail falls over the city 
Poor us trapped inside.

Puppies under rain 
So many smells, tiny teeth 
Here comes the baby!

Upgraded again 
Terrified of thermal grease 
It's working so far...

Many things, one place 
Stretch so thin, can barely think 
Welcome to grad school

Rushing here and there 
Meetings, puppies, and dinner 
Ending a long day

Eating lunch early 
I don't want to teach hungry 
Already worried

Exhaustion creeping 
From every direction 
Training is so hard

Running with Kitty 
Harder than I remember 
Legs now turned to gel

Racing against clouds 
Chopping blades, fall under foot 
A cold brew after

Why, oh why Vim? Why? 
Unintuitive as hell 
Who the hell made this?!

Too much fun last night 
Paying for it this morning 
Time to sleep one off

Reprieve from the rain 
No time for relaxation 
Must chop them all down!

D&D once more 
Plunging the bottomless depths 
Death behind that rock!

Chores are hard to do 
A baby  makes it so hard

The answer is yes

Now get my drink on

Distances measured

Drowsy, sweet morn

Sugar brings the friends

Such a give and take of time

Sleeping in til 3

steals all my chances for rest

coworker early in the  
morning sucks huge ass

nice nice nice nice nice

ment. Isn't that weird?
